  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book \"Logic of Experimentation: Rethinking Music Performance Through Artistic Research,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2018, offers a fresh perspective on music performance. Although it has not garnered citations or online mentions, its foundational insights into artistic research are likely to influence future scholarly discussions within the field.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published in 2018, \"Logic of Experimentation: Rethinking Music Performance Through Artistic Research\" by Leuven University Press stands as an innovative contribution to the field of music studies, particularly within the context of artistic research. While the book currently has no recorded citations or mentions across public platforms, it serves as a foundational work that could foster future academic discourse around the methodologies of music performance.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The lack of online engagement metrics, including mentions on platforms such as Wikipedia and Reddit, suggests that the book has not yet reached a broader audience outside traditional academic circles. This could indicate an area where increased visibility and outreach efforts may help enhance its impact and engagement with both scholarly and lay audiences.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of quantitative impact indicators, the thematic depth and unique approach presented in the book may play a crucial role in shaping upcoming research directions. It focuses on the interplay between experimentation and performance, which is a pertinent topic in the evolving landscape of music studies and artistic research.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In summary, while \"Logic of Experimentation\" has yet to achieve significant academic traction through citations or public discourse, it holds the potential to inspire future researchers and performers. As scholarly conversations around artistic methodologies continue to expand, the insights offered by this work may emerge as influential contributions in reshaping music performance studies.</p>",
